								Search Funds							





RHV has invested in 40 Search Funds since 2008. RHV has several investments in operating companies acquired by our Search Funds, and we regularly have 10 to 15  Search Funds actively seeking to acquire an operating business.
A Search Fund is a pool of capital raised to financially support the efforts of an entrepreneur, or a team of entrepreneurs, to locate a privately held company to acquire. Acquisitions are primarily financed by capital provided by the search fund investors.
RHV has the capacity to invest up to $4 million in a subsequent search fund acquisition. We have no minimum investment size, and the investment size is determined based on the Search Fund’s governing documents.
RHV can bring debt financing to the table through existing banking relationships and through HV Capital Investors, LLC, which is controlled by RHV’s investors. HVCI has a long track record of lending into the lower middle market, which includes providing loans to support search fund acquisitions.
Our Principals have a unique blend of experience that provides a basis to add value to operating companies acquired by Search Funds. That experience includes Board of Directors (public and private), owner-manager, operations, finance, information technology, banking and investment banking. RHV’s Principals are prepared to serve on the Board of Directors of the companies acquired, if requested by the search fund entrepreneur.
RHV Capital has investments in the following active Search Funds:







